
The daxfixmlfile program takes one or more XML file and prints or
executes the resulting commands.
Normally the used firewall is autodetected, and the resulting rules
are just printed to stdout.
With the "-f firewall" option, you can force daxfixmlfile to use the
given firewall.
With the "-x" switch the rules are executed.

E.g.:

# daxfixmlfile -f ipchains /etc/daxfid/xmlrules.d/identd.xml
ipchains -A INPUT -j REJECT -l --source %REMOTE_IP/255.255.255.255 --destination %LOCAL_IP/255.255.255.255 --destination-port 113 -p 6

# daxfixmlfile -f ipfwadm /etc/daxfid/xmlrules.d/loopback.xml
ipfwadm -a accept  -W lo
ipfwadm -a accept  lo

# daxfixmlfile -f iptables /etc/daxfid/xmlrules.d/martians.xml 
iptables -A INPUT -m limit -j LOG --in-interface %INTERFACE --source 127.0.0.0/255.0.0.0 %DAXFI --limit 10000 --limit-burst 10
iptables -A INPUT --in-interface %INTERFACE --source 127.0.0.0/255.0.0.0 -j DROP
iptables -A INPUT -m limit -j LOG --in-interface %INTERFACE --source %LOCAL_IP/255.255.255.255 %DAXFI --limit 10000 --limit-burst 10
iptables -A INPUT --in-interface %INTERFACE --source %LOCAL_IP/255.255.255.255 -j DROP

# daxfixmlfile -f ipfilter /etc/daxfid/xmlrules.d/igmp.xml
block in log quick proto 2 from %REMOTE_IP/255.255.255.255 to %LOCAL_IP/255.255.255.255


